==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Germ theory
<hw>Germ theory</hw>. <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The theory
that living organisms can be produced only by the development of living
germs. Cf. <er>Biogenesis</er>, <er>Abiogenesis</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The theory which attributes
contagious and infectious diseases, suppurative lesions, etc., to the
agency of germs, i.e. pathogenic microorganisms. The science of
bacteriology was developed after this theory had been
established.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Germule</ent>⟦br⟧
